name: Biology
subject: Sciences
description: Introductory college-level biology covering evolution, cellular processes, genetics, ecology, and systems interactions.
units: Chemistry of Life:8-11%,Cells:10-13%,Cellular Energetics:12-16%,Cell Communication & Cell Cycle:10-15%,Heredity:8-11%,Gene Expression & Regulation:12-16%,Natural Selection:13-20%,Ecology:10-15%

name: Chemistry
subject: Sciences
description: College-level general chemistry covering atomic structure, bonding, reactions, kinetics, thermodynamics, and equilibrium.
units: Atomic Structure & Properties:7-9%,Molecular & Ionic Compounds:7-9%,Intermolecular Forces & Properties:18-22%,Chemical Reactions:7-9%,Kinetics:7-9%,Thermodynamics:7-9%,Equilibrium:7-9%,Acids & Bases:11-15%,Applications of Thermodynamics:7-9%
bigIdeas: Scale, Proportion, and Quantity,Structure and Properties,Transformations,Energy
prerequisites: High school chemistry and Algebra II
labRequirement: 25% of time in labs; at least 16 labs (6 inquiry-based)

name: Environmental Science
subject: Sciences
description: Interdisciplinary study of ecological processes, Earth systems, human impacts, and sustainability.
units: Ecosystems:6-8%,Biodiversity:6-8%,Populations:10-15%,Earth Systems & Resources:10-15%,Land & Water Use:10-15%,Energy Resources & Consumption:10-15%,Atmospheric Pollution:7-10%,Aquatic & Terrestrial Pollution:7-10%,Global Change:15-20%
bigIdeas: Energy Transfer,Earth System Interactions,Species & Environment Interactions,Sustainability
prerequisites: Two years of lab science; one year algebra

name: Physics 1
subject: Sciences
description: Algebra-based physics covering kinematics, dynamics, energy, momentum, rotation, oscillations, and fluids.

name: Physics 2
subject: Sciences
description: Algebra-based physics covering thermodynamics, electricity, circuits, magnetism, optics, and modern physics.
units: Thermodynamics:10-12%,Electric Force, Field, & Potential:18-22%,Electric Circuits:10-14%,Magnetism & Electromagnetism:10-12%,Geometric & Physical Optics:12-14%,Quantum, Atomic, & Nuclear Physics:10-12%,Fluids:10-12%
prerequisites: AP Physics 1 or similar; concurrent Precalculus

name: Physics C: Electricity and Magnetism
subject: Sciences
description: Calculus-based study of electrostatics, capacitors, circuits, magnetic fields, and electromagnetism.

name: Physics C: Mechanics
subject: Sciences
description: Calculus-based mechanics covering kinematics, Newton’s laws, energy, momentum, rotation, oscillations, and gravitation.
units: Kinematics:14-20%,Newton’s Laws of Motion:17-23%,Work, Energy, & Power:14-17%,Systems of Particles & Linear Momentum:14-17%,Circular Motion & Rotation:14-20%,Oscillations:6-14%,Gravitation:6-14%
